modules.description: This module enables blocking reads from input sources like files and sockets in both binary and text modes, offering low-level access to bytes and characters as well as high-level functions for reading integers, lines, and entire files. It operates on `In_channel.t` values—custom blocks wrapping OC

This module handles input and output operations for standard channels, supporting formatted output, string manipulation, and S-expression serialization. It works with `In_channel.t` and `Out_channel.t` types to enable reading from and writing to terminals, files, or external processes. You can read lines from standard input, write structured data to standard output, or serialize values for debugging and inter-process communication. Submodules extend this functionality with fine-grained control over input parsing and binary data handling.
